<L>__{exterior parched countryside the lion}
<A>__{the tribe slowly wanders across the bare, flat countryside foraging for roots and occasional berries. eight of them are irregularly strung out on the open plain, about fifty feet apart. the ground is flat for miles around. suddenly, moonwatcher becomes aware of a lion, stalking them about 300 yards away. defenceless and with nowhere to hide, they scatter in all directions, but the lion brings one to the ground.}
